## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates incident triage skills in a real multi-region AWS setup, focusing on identifying root causes under pressure, deciding rapid mitigations, and confirming with telemetry. It tests familiarity with ALB, NAT, RDS, Route53, and CloudWatch/X-Ray.

## Key Concepts
- Multi-region deployment
- Incident triage
- ALB, NAT gateway, RDS latency
- CloudWatch, VPC Flow Logs, X-Ray
- DR planning

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo-logic for triage steps in a real incident
function triage(incident) {
  // fetch metrics from CloudWatch and X-Ray
  // check ALB target health and NAT quotas
  // identify root cause and apply mitigation
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- Which metrics would you alert on for cross-region failures?
- How would you automate the triage workflow?
